{"article_id":"960PYa1q6UyB2pxd","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The U.S. unemployment rate unexpectedly dropped to 13.3 percent in May , down from a record high in April ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"indicating","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"the nation 's economy is recovering faster","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"than expected from the coronavirus lockdown .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"The Labor Department said in its Friday report","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that employers added a stunning 2.5 million jobs in May","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"-- the biggest increase on record .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"The economy shed a combined 22.1 million jobs in April and March ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"meaning there are an estimated 21 million Americans currently out of work .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Stocks in this Article","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"I :","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"DJI DOW JONES AVERAGES $ 26989.99 -282.31","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"( -1.04 % )","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"SP500 S & P 500","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"$ 3190.14 -17.04","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"( -0.53 % )","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"I : COMP NASDAQ COMPOSITE INDEX","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"$ 10020.346202 +66.59","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"( +0.67 % )","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Economists","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"surveyed by Refinitiv","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"expected the report ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"conducted in mid-May ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"to show","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"that unemployment rose to 19.8 percent in May","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"and that employers shed 8 million jobs .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"If the expectation had been accurate ,","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"it would have been the worst figure since the Great Depression .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"US JOB GROWTH ROARED BACK IN MAY :","depth":4},{"id":29,"text":"THESE INDUSTRIES SAW THE BIGGEST GAINS","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"\" Barring a second surge of Covid-19 ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"the overall U.S. economy may have turned a corner ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"as evidenced by the surprise job gains today ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"even though it still remains to be seen exactly what the new normal will look like , ''","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"said Tony Bedikian , head of global markets at Citizens Bank .","depth":4},{"id":35,"text":"KUDLOW SAYS","depth":3},{"id":36,"text":"NEXT CORONAVIRUS RELIEF PACKAGE NEEDS TO INCLUDE 'LONG-TERM ' MEASURES","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"TO SUPPORT ECONOMY","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"The jobless rate dropped from 14.7 percent in April ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"which was the highest level ever","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"since record-keeping began in 1948 .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"The surprise decline ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"combined with the surge in jobs ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"suggests","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"the worst is over for the nation 's economy","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"as states ease stay-at-home guidelines","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"and businesses bring back staff .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Stocks roared higher","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"following the report ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"with the Dow Jones Industrial Average pointing to an open nearly 600 higher .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"`` Today was a shocking jobs number","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"- and for the first time this year it was a positive shock , ''","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"said Chris Zaccarelli , chief investment officer for Independent Advisor Alliance .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"`` It ' s very encouraging to see","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"workers being recalled back by their employers","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"and the unemployment rate dropped back down in May . ''","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Leisure and hospitality , the sector","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"hit hardest by the outbreak of the virus ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"accounted for almost half of the increase ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"with more than 1.2 million employees returning to their jobs last month .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"In April , the industry lost a staggering 7.6 million jobs .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"More than 1.3 million workers returned to food services and drinking places","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"as states gradually allowed businesses","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"deemed nonessential","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"to reopen .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Construction also saw a significant jump in employment last month :","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"The sector added 464,000 jobs .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Education and health services increased by 424,000","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"and retail climbed by 368,000 .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The number of unemployed Americans","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"who reported","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"being temporarily laid off","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"decreased by 2.7 million in May ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"representing the majority of the jobs","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that returned .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"Among those","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"who said","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"they were not temporarily laid off ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"the number of permanent job losses continued to increase ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"rising by 295,000 in May to 2.3 million .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Over the course of the past few weeks , every state has started to navigate reopening their economies .","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"But the unemployment level ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"which remains at the highest level since the Depression ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"is expected to remain elevated","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"as social distancing guidelines remain in place .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"`` It 's important to remember","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"the labor market still faces an unemployment rate at the highest level since the Great Depression with tens of millions of Americans still out of work , ''","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"said Daniel Zhao , a Glassdoor senior economist .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"`` While the labor market may be on the path to recovery ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"there is still a long way to go","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"until the labor market returns to pre-crisis levels","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"and makes up for lost growth . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":183,"left":126,"right":182,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":119,"right":125,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":119,"left":100,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":95,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":0,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":1,"right":93,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":93,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":97,"right":98,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":4,"right":96,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":96,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":109,"right":117,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":109,"left":9,"right":108,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":108,"left":10,"right":107,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":107,"left":101,"right":106,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":101,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":103,"right":105,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":103,"left":13,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":